# Simulated ARGs

For simulated ARGs, we ran with 10 and 100 trees, the latter produced the best results.
We also ran with random initialization and INIT_TRUTH=1 (which, as expected, produced the best results,
since the solver starts from the true parameters values and then finds the maximum likelihood solution
by searching from there).

Our reported results are from:
```
INIT_TRUTH=1 TREES100=1 python glike.aa5.nomig.py aa5.nomig_50.simdata/aa5.nomig_50_sim__0-0.trees aa5.nomig_50.simdata/aa5.nomig_50_sim__0-0.trees.popmap.json
```

# tsinfer ARGs

We used the same configuration as with the simulated ARGs, except we needed to skip certain
trees that caused gLike to throw exceptions, so while we requested 100 trees, we skipped 5 of
them due to this (TSINFER=1 skips a hardcoded list of trees).

```
TSINFER=1 INIT_TRUTH=1 TREES100=1 python glike.aa5.nomig.py aa5.nomig.tsi/aa5.nomig_50_tsi_aa5.nomig_50_sim__0-0.trees.vcz.tsdate.trees aa5.nomig_50.simdata/aa5.nomig_50_sim__0-0.trees.popmap.json
```
